342
00:31:14,080 --> 00:31:15,520
I'm Maria.

343
00:31:15,520 --> 00:31:19,360
I'm the local manager of the Central Region for Atlantic Life Insurance Company.

344
00:31:19,360 --> 00:31:20,440
Hello.

345
00:31:20,440 --> 00:31:22,940
Central Region?

346
00:31:22,940 --> 00:31:24,840
Local manager?

347
00:31:24,840 --> 00:31:27,580
Madam... Madam Maria.

348
00:31:27,580 --> 00:31:29,540
Madam Maria, what brings you here?

349
00:31:29,540 --> 00:31:31,880
- Have a seat. 
 - All right.

350
00:31:31,880 --> 00:31:33,240
Here's the thing.

351
00:31:33,240 --> 00:31:36,780
Our customer service department received a call from a client named Henry.

352
00:31:36,780 --> 00:31:39,500
He said he wanted to buy insurance for himself and his siblings.

353
00:31:39,500 --> 00:31:41,900
He specified you as his agent.

354
00:31:41,900 --> 00:31:43,940
I couldn't get through to your phone.

355
00:31:43,940 --> 00:31:45,160
After asking colleagues in Yan City,

356
00:31:45,160 --> 00:31:47,300
I learned you were attending a wedding in your hometown.

357
00:31:47,300 --> 00:31:49,500
I was afraid the client might go elsewhere if we kept him waiting,

358
00:31:49,500 --> 00:31:51,420
so I came personally.

359
00:31:51,420 --> 00:31:55,260
I've brought the client's documents and requirements

360
00:31:55,260 --> 00:31:57,960
to help you tailor the insurance plans.

361
00:31:57,960 --> 00:32:00,760
This... This is really appreciated.

362
00:32:00,760 --> 00:32:03,380
Thank you so much for coming personally.

363
00:32:03,380 --> 00:32:05,140
So heartwarming.

364
00:32:05,140 --> 00:32:07,060
This is the power of our team.

365
00:32:07,060 --> 00:32:08,780
Madam, please enjoy your tea.

366
00:32:08,780 --> 00:32:11,600
I'll go check the client details inside.

367
00:32:11,600 --> 00:32:14,000
Take your time.

368
00:32:15,460 --> 00:32:17,200
Jenny.

369
00:32:18,360 --> 00:32:19,660
Yes, Ma'am?

370
00:32:19,660 --> 00:32:22,060
This village looks festive.

371
00:32:22,060 --> 00:32:24,145
Preparing for a wedding?

372
00:32:24,145 --> 00:32:25,200
Yes.

373
00:32:25,200 --> 00:32:27,600
I've never seen a wedding with so many flowers.

374
00:32:27,600 --> 00:32:29,060
In the city, weddings are all handled

375
00:32:29,060 --> 00:32:30,520
by wedding planning companies.

376
00:32:30,520 --> 00:32:32,540
They end up looking the same.

377
00:32:32,540 --> 00:32:35,300
Yours here in the mountains is better. It's unique.

378
00:32:35,300 --> 00:32:36,380
Exactly.

379
00:32:36,380 --> 00:32:39,320
We have lots of traditional rituals for weddings in the mountains.

380
00:32:39,320 --> 00:32:41,940
Just the banquet alone lasts three days.

381
00:32:41,940 --> 00:32:44,320
- Banquet? 
 - Yes.

382
00:32:46,900 --> 00:32:49,740
Now that you mention it, I am a little hungry.

383
00:32:49,740 --> 00:32:53,580
Then, stay for the feast, Ma'am.

384
00:32:53,580 --> 00:32:55,620
- Would that be all right? 
 - Of course.

385
00:32:55,620 --> 00:32:58,640
The more, the merrier. Just an extra seat.

386
00:33:13,740 --> 00:33:15,600
I really shouldn't impose.

387
00:33:15,600 --> 00:33:17,800
At least stay for a toast.

388
00:33:17,800 --> 00:33:20,960
- Stay for a toast. 
 - Why are there four armchairs there?

389
00:33:20,960 --> 00:33:22,540
The bride and groom were both orphans.

390
00:33:22,540 --> 00:33:24,800
Those armchairs will stand in for their parents.

391
00:33:24,800 --> 00:33:26,300
- Thank you. 
 - Thank you.

392
00:33:26,300 --> 00:33:27,820
